{{Infobox saint | name = Abhor and Mehraela | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | titles = Martyrs | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | home_town = | residence = | death_date = | death_place = | venerated_in = Coptic Orthodox Church [[Roman Catholic Church]] | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | major_shrine = | feast_day = January 9 | attributes = | patronage = | issues = | suppressed_date = | suppressed_by = | influences = | influenced = | tradition = | major_works = }} '''Abhor''' (or '''Amba Hor''') and '''Mehraela''' were a brother and sister who were [[martyr]]s for the [[Christian faith]]. Etymology of the word "Abhor": from Latin ''abhorrēre'' (to shudder at, shrink from), from "ab" (away) and "horrēre" (to bristle, shudder).<ref>[https://educalingo.com/en/dic-en/abhor/ Meaning of "abhor" in the English dictionary] Retrieved on 17 Feb 2018</ref> The book of their "acts" has been lost. Their [[feast day]] is celebrated on January 9 in the [[Coptic Orthodox Church of Alexandria|Coptic Church]].
