[[File:Adlersiegel Herzog Adalbert von Teck (um 1190).jpg|thumb | Eagle seal of Adalbert, Duke of Teck ({{circa|1190}})]]

'''Adalbert I, Duke of Teck''', ({{circa|1135}} &ndash; {{circa|1195}}) was a German nobleman.   After the death of his brother [[Berthold IV, Duke of Zahringen|Berthold IV]], he styled himself ''Duke of Teck'', and thus founded the elder line of the [[Dukes of Teck]], which would exist until 1439.

== Life ==
He was a son of Duke [[Conrad I, Duke of Zähringen|Conrad I]] of Zähringen and his wife Clementia of Luxembourg-Namur.   He was named after his maternal uncle.

When his brother [[Berthold IV, Duke of Zahringen|Berthold IV]] died in 1186, he inherited the family possessions in the foothills of the [[Swabian Jura]], including [[Teck]] Castle and the office of [[Cup-bearer]] of the [[Abbey of St. Gall]] and the area on the upper [[Neckar]] that went with this office.

He is first mentioned as the son of Duke Conrad I in a document dated 1146; in 1152, he is named as a younger brother of Duke Berthold IV.  In May 1189, he is first mentioned as Duke of Teck ({{lang|la|Dux de Tecke}}) in a document of Emperor [[Henry VI, Holy Roman Emperor|Henry VI]].

A Duke "Adalbert of Teck" is also mentioned on 20 June 1192 in [[Schwäbisch Gmünd]], on 4 (or 10) December 1193 in [[Gelnhausen]] and on 12 December 1193 at the court of Henry VI in [[Frankfurt am Main|Frankfurt]], in a document of Count [[Egino IV, Count of Urach|Egino IV]] of Urach about [[Bebenhausen Abbey]], and by Bishop [[Diethelm of Krenkingen|Diethelm]] of [[Bishopric of Constance|Constance]] in 1192.  However, it is not clear whether these are references to Adalbert I or to his son, [[Adalbert II, Duke of Teck|Adalbert II]].

When his brother Hugh, Duke of Ullenburg died, Adalbert inherited his possessions in the [[Ortenau]] and the [[Breisgau]].  He may have already held the office of Treasurer of the [[Bishopric of Basel]].

== Marriage and issue ==
Adalbert I was married to a noblewoman named Adelaide.  Her parentage is unknown.  They had the following children:
* [[Adalbert II, Duke of Teck|Adalbert II]] (d. {{circa|1215/1219}})
* (?) Agatha, married Diepold, Count of Lechsgemünd (d. after 1192)
* (?) Matilda

