{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox AFL biography | name = Roy Bent | image = File:Roy_Bent_Norwood.jpg | alt = | caption = | fullname = Roy Edward Kimberley Bent | nickname = Cool Alec | birth_date = 1900 | birth_place = [[Broken Hill, New South Wales]] | death_date = {{Death_date_and_given_age|1975|10|7|75|df=y}} | death_place = [[Mount Gambier, South Australia]] | originalteam = North Broken Hill<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article45561213 |title=Football. |newspaper=[[Barrier Miner]] |location=Broken Hill, NSW |date=20 July 1921 |accessdate=20 June 2015 |page=3 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref> | height = | weight = | position = [[Australian rules football positions|Full Forward]] | guernsey = 20, 26 | statsend = 1928 | years1 = 1921 – 1928 | club1 = [[Norwood Football Club|Norwood]] | games_goals1 = 98 (333) | sooteam1 = [[South Australia Australian rules football team|South Australia]] | soogames_goals1 = 17 (60) | careerhighlights = *2x [[Norwood Football Club|Norwood]] premiership player (1922, 1925) *4x [[SANFL]] leading goal kicker (1921, 1924, 1925, 1926) *5x [[Norwood Football Club|Norwood]] leading goalkicker }}
'''Roy Bent''' (1900 – 7 October 1975) was an [[Australian rules]] footballer who played with the [[Norwood Football Club]] in the [[South Australian National Football League|South Australian Football Association]]. He was the competitions leading goal kicker on four occasions 1921, 1924, 1925 and 1926. Late in the 1923 minor round Roy Bent was suspended for six matches for throwing the ball at a boundary umpire and 'bruising his chest'.<ref name="Redlegs">{{cite web|url=http://www.redlegsmuseum.com.au/ON_FIELD/PLAYERS/BENT__Roy.aspx|title=REDLEGS MUSEUM - PLAYERS|publisher=Redlegsmuseum.com.au|accessdate=22 November 2014}}</ref> Later in the year he was jokingly awarded a leather medal in remembrance of his suspension.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://genes.mcclimont.id.au/individual.php?pid=I44&ged=mcclimont|title=Roy Edward Kimberley "Cool Alec" Bent 1900–1975 - McClimont - Cox Family Tree|publisher=Genes.mcclimont.id.au|accessdate=22 November 2014}}</ref> He was killed in a car accident in 1975.<ref name="Redlegs"/>
