{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}} {{Use British English|date=April 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = W. Brady | image = | fullname = | birth_date = | birth_place = Scotland | death_date = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | years1 = 1887 | clubs1 = [[Renton F.C.|Renton]] | caps1 = ? |goals1 = ? | years2 = 1888-1889 | clubs2 = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | caps2 = 9 |goals2 = 2 | years3 = 1889 | clubs3 = [[Newcastle West End F.C.|Newcastle West End]]| caps3 = ? |goals3 = ? }} '''W. Brady''' was a [[Scottish people|Scottish]] [[association football|footballer]] who played in [[the Football League]] for [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Joyce|first=Michael|title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939|year=2004|publisher=SoccerData|isbn=1-899468-67-6}}</ref>
==Playing Career== W Brady was signed by [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] in December 1888 and made his debut at Turf Moor, Burnley, on 08-Dec-1888 against [[Stoke F.C.|Stoke]]. He was selected to play inside-right in place of [[Willie McKay]] who moved to inside-left. He made an immediate impact. In a "strong fought physical encounter" play often stopped for injury. After one such break W Brady got the ball and put Burnley ahead and it remained 1-0 at half-time. The second half was more even but Burnley managed to go 2-0 up on the hour. Both sides pressed but defences held until Stoke guaranteed an exciting finish by making 2-1 with ten minutes left. The Burnley defence held on and got an important win.<ref>{{cite book|last=Metcalf|first=Mark|title=The Origins of the Football League|year=2013|publisher=Amberley|isbn=978 1 4456 1881 4}}</ref>
Brady was ever-present from the Stoke game and played 9 times and scored 2 goals. He played 7 times at inside-right and twice at outside-right. Brady also played in both FA Cup ties played by Burnley in 1889 and he scored in the First Round tie against Old Westminsters which Burnley won 4-3. Burnley finished 9th in the League and scored 42 goals in 22 games. Burnley were knocked out of the FA Cup in the Second Round by [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{cite web | title= English National Football Archive| first=| last=| url=http://www.enfa.co.uk//| accessdate=2018-01-11}} (registration & fee required)</ref>
